-- subscriptions_metrics.sql
SELECT 
    DATE_TRUNC('month', COALESCE(s.started_at, b.event_month))::DATE AS month,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'unknown') AS industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT u.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM subscriptions s
LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT 
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month ORDER BY event_id) AS rn
    FROM billing_events
) b ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id 
    AND b.rn = 1
    AND b.event_month >= s.started_at
    AND (s.ended_at IS NULL OR b.event_month < s.ended_at)
WHERE s.status = 'active'
GROUP BY 
    DATE_TRUNC('month', COALESCE(s.started_at, b.event_month))::DATE,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'unknown'),
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'unknown')
ORDER BY month, tier, industry;
